args:
Some months have passed since the Other took
Zethia's body and ascended the imperial throne.
The prince despairs but continues the fight for
his people. When the fourth heir, Valyx, attacks,
the Halidom musters its defense.
We failed to save Zethia at the Binding Ruins\nand returned to the Halidom in defeat.
No one said a word along the road home,\nand the cruel, alien expression on Zethia's\nface was never far from my mind.
I cursed my impotence with every step.\nNever had a homecoming felt more like\na coward's flight.
Dys fahr Dyrenell! Dys fahr Dyrenell!
Hear me, men! Emperor Aurelius is fallen,\nsacrificed at the altar of Dyrenell's return.
But the Empire will not stop to grieve this\ndeath, for it is as insignificant as his reign!
I now rule as your Empress Zethia,\nbut do not think of this as a mere\nsuccession.
I will EXCEED him! I will impress a new\norder on this land and all the world: bend\nthe knee to Dyrenell, or be destroyed!
I will acknowledge no rule save mine!\nIf a village resists, put it to the torch!\nLet no rebellious stone stand atop another!
All dragons are to be bound in chains,\nfor we rule over man and mana both!\nLet none usurp our power!
Oi, it's the Empire! This town's done for!\nRun! RUUUN!
The prince of the Mistholt'll shelter us!\nEveryone 'ead there now!
The Other laid claim to the body of the prince's\nbeloved sister, Zethia, who now styles herself\nthe Auspex of the Nether.
Some months after her ascension to the throne...
I wanted to brief you on the latest news\nof Zethia, Your Highness.
In the short time since her return to the\ncapital, she has brought the entire\nkingdom to heel.
She is now empress in name and\nsubstance both.
That's troubling. If she's in the capital,\nwe can't easily move on her.
And what about the woman who looked\nlike Zethia? The one who told me to\n＂seek the Dawnshard.＂
We've searched all manner of tomes,\nbut we don't even know what it IS,\nmuch less where to find it.
Zethia was within my reach, Elly.\nI was so close to saving her,\nbut now... I just don't know.
First you must find the steel in your spine,\nYour Highness, for you are the axis upon\nwhich this entire castle turns!
If you lose hope, all who look to you will \nalso succumb. You cannot afford to\nindulge in despair!
You're right, Elly—and I'm sorry. I know\nthis place is the last bastion for those who\nsuffer under the Empire's rule.
Keeping them safe is our first priority.
I've said nothing to earn such thanks.\nI'm merely relieved to see you take heart.
Bad news, {player_name}!\nWe got company at the walls,\nand they ain't lookin' too friendly.
No. An imperial platoon—not that there's\nmuch of a difference at this point.\nThey fly Dyrenell's hideous colors.
With a greatbear's mug slapped on top!\nGotta admit, these guys look tougher'n—
Then I guess Valyx has finally come.
The fourth heir to Alberia. ...My brother.
I'm the seventh child, Emile was the sixth,\nand Valyx is above him as fourthborn.
We're seven in total, so there are three\nahead of him in the line of succession.
Hold a moment. You said Valyx is fourth in\nline, and Emile is sixth. What happened to\nthe fifth?
I don't know. I'm actually not sure anyone\nknows, even within my family.
Something happened before my time.\nThat's all I can tell you.
That's great, but right now, we got number\nfour beatin' down our front door.
I'll hand it to him—takes serious guts to\nattack a castle head-on like this.
Head-on? Wait, he's attacking the\nfront gates?
How is that possible? The path to the front\ngates is protected by the Windwyrm's\nwall of gales.
How could he have pushed through,\nlet alone with a large-scale force?
Perhaps the power of my wind was\ninsufficient.
It may be time to seek a wind dracolith\nto bolster my power.
We'll need to reopen the Windway,\nwhich means routing our assailants first.
I can't imagine pushing through the\nWindwyrm's mana by force.
Your brother must be equal parts brute\nstrength and hubris.
He's certainly strong, but Valyx is also\nquite humble. ...Or used to be, at any rate.
And he's certainly not one that would\nhappily submit to evil.
Someone else may be leading his men.
An ambitious lieutenant, perhaps.\nOr some other newly appointed dog.
Well, whoever it is, they ain't leavin'.
Their intrusion has already set the fiends\nof the forest on edge.
All right. Get ready, everyone.\nWe'll put down the fiends and\nmeet the Empire head-on.
